## 
In Sprint 1
Our team focused on the planning stage of the projects. We collected user stories and prioritized the important features for the application. After that, we specified the system scope and identified the actors and use cases.We created Use Case Diagram (UML) that show how users interact with the system. We also designed basic wireframes for the Dashboard including the task and study planner pages. Lastly, we created the project folder structure to organize the files.
In Sprint 2
Our team continued working on the design and development of the application. We created additional wireframes for the Nudge feature and the home page with other pages. We improve the prototype based on feedback from Sprint 1. We also developed additional features for the application and collected feedback from testers and team members. Functional testing was conducted and the progress was committed to Github. At the end of the sprint, we held a sprint review meeting.
InSprint 3
The team finalized the working prototype of the application. Final testing was handled to make sure the system works properly. We take screenshots of the final prototype for the report. We also prepared the final documentation and organized the Github repository and project folders. Lastly, presentation slides were created and all Trello and Github evidence were compiled.
